rksheet.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "1.  Graphing functions and the \+
" }{TEXT 257 4 "plot" }{TEXT -1 89 " command.  The Maple command for p
lotting the graph of an explicitly defined function is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }{TEXT 258 0 "
" }{TEXT 259 4 "plot" }{TEXT 260 0 "" }{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 261 4 "e
xpr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 266 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 20 "=range [, options
]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "whe
re " }{TEXT 262 4 "expr" }{TEXT 267 1 " " }{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic \+
expression" }{TEXT 264 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which represents the functi
on to be plotted and " }{TEXT 263 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 38 " is the independ
ent variable used in  " }{TEXT 265 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define \+
the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 81 "Several options exist to change way the plot will appear.
  These options include:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 126 "            y=range                       this al
lows the user to specifiy the range of output values which Maple will \+
display" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "            thickness=value  \+
         this controls the thickness of the plotted curve.  value = 1,
 2, 3, 4, or 5" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 119 "            color=valu
e                 this sets the color of the plotted curve.  value = r
ed, green, blue, cyan, etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 160 "For each of the following functions provide a \+
plot to represent the graph the function.  Choose a range that will op
timally represent the features of the graph." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "a.    y = 3x - 1" }}{EXCHG 
