" {TEXT -1 71 "b.f8 is positive (-infinity,2) and (4, infinity)\nc.f8 \+
is negative (2,4)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 25 "d.the y intercept is
 128 " }{TEXT 335 30 "kp this is correct on this one" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 41 "e. both ends limits are largely positive." }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 254 "3.  Polynomials: \+
 Local extreme values and monotonicity.  Beyond information of the typ
e gathered above about intercepts and signs of a polynomial,  other im
portant information can be determined from the so called \"critical po
ints\" of a polynomial.  The " }{TEXT 304 68 "critical points of a pol
ynomial are the intercepts of its derivative" }{TEXT -1 201 ".  Since \+
the derivative of a function at a point represents the slope of the ta
ngent line to the graph of the that function at the point, then the in
tercepts of the derivative are places where the the " }{TEXT 305 39 "t
angent lines to the function are flat," }{TEXT -1 11 " i.e., are " }
{TEXT 306 10 "horizontal" }{TEXT -1 37 " lines.  At such places the gr
aph is " }{TEXT 307 33 "neither increasing nor decreasing" }{TEXT -1 
83 ".  Elsewhere the graph must be either increasing or decreasing.  F
or a polynomial, " }{TEXT 303 102 "local extreme values (local maximum
s or local minimums) must occur at the intercepts of the derivative" }
{TEXT -1 3 ".  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 81 "     The following features are important in analyzing th
e graph of a polynomial:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 9 "     f.  " }{TEXT 308 17 " critical points " }
{TEXT -1 15 "of the function" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 54 "         \+
             For a polynomial these are the i" }{TEXT 309 28 "ntercept
s of the derivative " }{TEXT -1 17 "of the polynomial" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 17 "     g.    local " }{TEXT 310 14 "maximum points" }
{TEXT -1 28 " of the graph of a function " }{TEXT 311 8 "y = f(x)" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 88 "                      These are points (x
,y) on the graph of the function for which the " }{TEXT 312 32 "y-valu
e is locally the largest v" }{TEXT -1 68 "alue of the function.  Nearb
y values on the graph are lower.  For a " }{TEXT 313 24 "polynomials t
he x-value " }{TEXT -1 19 "of the point (x,y) " }{TEXT 314 25 "must be
 a critical point " }{TEXT -1 18 "of the polynomial." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 16 "     h.   local " }{TEXT 315 14 "minimum points" }
{TEXT -1 28 " of the graph of a function " }{TEXT 316 9 "y = f(x) " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 88 "                      These are points (x
,y) on the graph of the function for which the " }{TEXT 317 39 "y-valu
e is locally the smallest value o" }{TEXT -1 79 "f the function.  Near
by values on the graph are higher.  For a polynomials the " }{TEXT 
318 53 "x-value of the point (x,y) must be a critical point o" }{TEXT 
-1 17 "f the polynomial." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 72 "     i.    re
gions (intervals) in the domain of the function where the v" }{TEXT 
319 36 "alues of the function are increasing" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 48 "                       Those regions where the g" }{TEXT 320 
56 "raph rises as the graph is traversed from left to right." }{TEXT 
-1 82 "  For a continuous function, and in particular for polynomials,
 these regions are " }{TEXT 325 30 "bounded by the critical points" }
{TEXT -1 33 " and may stretch to +/- infinity." }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 61 "     j.    regions (intervals) in the domain of the funct
ion " }{TEXT 321 47 "where the values of the function are decreasing" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 47 "                       Those regions wh
ere the " }{TEXT 322 12 "graph falls " }{TEXT -1 27 "as the graph is t
raversed f" }{TEXT 323 18 "rom left to right." }{TEXT -1 82 "  For a c
ontinuous function, and in particular for polynomials, these regions a
re " }{TEXT 324 30 "bounded by the critical points" }{TEXT -1 33 " and
 may stretch to +/- infinity." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 50 "For each of the following polynomials,  p
rovide a " }{TEXT 326 24 "graph of the polynomial." }{TEXT -1 101 "  C
hoose a range that will optimally represent the features of the graph.
  Include the graph of the d" }{TEXT 328 10 "eriviative" }{TEXT -1 52 
" of the polynomial on the plot.   Plot the function " }{TEXT 327 7 "i
n red " }{TEXT -1 19 "and the derviative " }{TEXT 329 8 "in green" }
{TEXT -1 4 ".   " }{TEXT 269 4 "Also" }{TEXT -1 22 ", for each polynom
ial " }{TEXT 330 67 "find each of the above ten graphcial characterist
ics (a.  thru j.):" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
